      <bioghist id="ref9">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         <p>Robert Kaplan was the research director for the United Mine Workers Union of America (UMWA) from 1942 to 1967. He also served as the archivist in charge of documenting American labor leader John L. Lewis' term as president of the UMWA. As research director, Kaplan often contributed commentaries on economics and labor relations to the 
                <title render="italic" ns2:type="simple">UMWA Journal</title>.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref10">
         <head>Description of the Collection</head>
         <p>The collection consists of correspondence, research materials and unpublished writings of Robert Kaplan. The research materials and writings document John L. Lewis, the UMWA Welfare and Retirement Fund, and Josephine Roche, retirement fund director.</p>
      </scopecontent>
